"17_gc_full_tests.mst — GcFullTest (tests_s08.md §In-language tests, S8
 gate items 2-3). Adapted from the doc's own sketch: `Smalltalk gcFull` (not
 `System gcFull` — `Smalltalk` is the actual bound global, world/20_system.mst)
 and a plain identity-keyed `Dictionary` (not `IdentityDictionary`, which
 doesn't exist in this world — `Object>>hash` is `^self identityHash` and
 `Object>>=` is `^self == anObject`, so a plain Dictionary already IS
 identity-keyed for any object that doesn't override them, exactly the
 doc's own noted fallback)."

TestCase subclass: GcFullTest [
    runAll [
        self runTest: #testChurnWithGrowthAndRelease
            do: [ self testChurnWithGrowthAndRelease ].
        self runTest: #testLiveGraphIntactAfterGcFull
            do: [ self testLiveGraphIntactAfterGcFull ].
        self runTest: #testIdentityDictionaryAfterGcFull
            do: [ self testIdentityDictionaryAfterGcFull ].
    ]

    "Sustained churn (each batch of 100 abandoned wholesale) interleaved
     with growth, then a full GC — the surviving batch's own content must
     still be intact and reachable afterward. Deliberately small (300
     total, not thousands): this suite also runs under
     MACVM_GC_STRESS=1, where EVERY allocation scavenges, and debug
     builds run a full O(heap) verify pass on every scavenge's entry AND
     exit — late in this suite (after the whole world plus 16 other test
     classes have loaded), that heap is already substantial, so even a
     few hundred allocations here is enough coverage; a few thousand
     turned this one test into multiple minutes by itself."
    testChurnWithGrowthAndRelease [
        | keep sum |
        keep := OrderedCollection new.
        1 to: 300 do: [:i |
            (i \\ 100) = 1 ifTrue: [ keep := OrderedCollection new ].
            keep add: (Array with: i with: i * 2) ].
        Smalltalk gcFull.
        sum := 0.
        keep do: [:a | sum := sum + (a at: 1) ].
        self assert: sum > 0
    ]

    "A Dictionary's whole structure (backing key/value Arrays, every
     String value) must relocate consistently under compaction — every
     key must still resolve to its matching value, not a neighbor's."
    testLiveGraphIntactAfterGcFull [
        | d |
        d := Dictionary new.
        1 to: 100 do: [:i | d at: i put: i printString ].
        Smalltalk gcFull.
        Smalltalk gcFull.
        1 to: 100 do: [:i | self assert: (d at: i) equals: i printString ]
    ]

    "Identity, not equality: distinct Object instances used as Dictionary
     keys must still resolve to their own associated value after
     compaction moves them — this only works if identityHash truly
     survives (side-map channel, same as Smalltalk-level identityHash)
     and the Dictionary's own backing storage relocates in step with its
     keys."
    testIdentityDictionaryAfterGcFull [
        | keys d |
        keys := (1 to: 30) collect: [:i | Object new ].
        d := Dictionary new.
        keys doWithIndex: [:k :i | d at: k put: i ].
        Smalltalk gcFull.
        keys doWithIndex: [:k :i | self assert: (d at: k) equals: i ]
    ]
]
